{"author":{"id":"4c7dbda7c645778269782bed3653337b6b9b482f6bdbd9df9e78d2b457887976"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1742658935,"nonce":"F7PqPDVs/CV/H/2ZrpD52/nZUR4=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOCGKeh86vQ-7P","github-url":"https://github.com/git-bug/git-bug/issues/1330","origin":"github"},"title":"README says to set up a bridge with `new`, but the correct command appears to be `configure`","message":"Hi there,\n\njust setting up this project and following the README guide, I hit the following snag. It says to add a bridge with \n\n```\ngit bug bridge new\n```\n\nhowever, that yields:\n\n```\nError: unknown command \"new\" for \"git-bug bridge\"\n```\n\nUsing the `--help` option, it appears that the correct sub-command is `configure`, and indeed, that works. I'd started a pull request fixing the README, but I thought maybe this a discrepancy between the state of the code and the release, so I figured I tell you here \n\nCheerz, and cool project :)","files":null}]}